                      "summary": "An Account Funding Transaction is required for reloading prepaid cards and in card-absent environments for various purposes including person-to-person money transfers, disbursements from Visa Corporate Cards, and funding digital wallets. Effective January 20, 2024, it will include the purchase of liquid and cryptocurrency assets. In the U.S., it can be used for domestic transactions involving non-fiat currency with debit or prepaid cards until January 19, 2024. The transaction must include a specific indicator and comply with Visa Direct AFT Processing Guide, and it cannot be used for payments for goods or services (except Visa Scan to Pay), funding merchant accounts, or debt repayment."
                    },
